            </rs>. The Prosecutor deposed <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="172012070009"></xptr> that the Prisoner brought a Letter to him and another Paper as from the Earl of Sunderland, saying that the Earl sent him with it, and that he (the Prisoner) was his Nephew; that he askt the Prisoner whether he was the Earl's Brother's or his Sister's Son: to which he answered, that he was his Brother's Son, and that his Name was Spencer; then he told the Prisoner that he knew my Lord's Family too well to be imposed upon by him, and that my Lord had no Brother. That the Prisoner at last confest the Cheat, and that one Conner (a Prisoner) put him upon it. Sheriff Billers deposed that the Prisoner served him such a Trick and got Two Guineas out of him. The Prisoner behaved himself very impudently to the Court, the Evidences, etc. The Jury found him <rs id="t17201207-52-verdict277" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17201207-52-verdict277" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. And it appearing that he had been twice convicted for the like Offence before, and had been Fined, and Imprisoned for it, all which not being sufficient to reclaim him. The Court <rs id="t17201207-52-punish278" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17201207-52-punish278" type="punishmentCategory" value="miscPunish"></interp>
